This paper deals with the design of pricing mechanisms for multi-unit markets, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of game theory (cs.GT), algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), economics and computation (cs.EC), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper uses mathematical and computational techniques to analyze the performance of different pricing strategies, which is a common approach in these sub-fields.
